\[z^7 + z^6 + z^5 + z^4 + z^3 + z^2 + z + 1 = \frac{z^8 - 1}{z - 1}.\]Thus, the roots of the polynomial are the eighth roots of unity, excluding 1.  These roots lie on the unit circle, and form a regular heptagon.

