The area of a regular heptagon with side length $s$ is
\[\frac{7s^2}{4} \cot \frac{180^\circ}{7}.\]Let $z = \operatorname{cis} \theta,$ where $0 < \theta < 360^\circ.$  Then
\[z^7 = \operatorname{cis} 7 \theta = 1.\]Hence, $7 \theta$ is a multiple of $360^\circ,$ so $\theta$ is a multiple of $\frac{360^\circ}{7}.$

