The side length of the heptagon is
\[2 \sin \frac{180^\circ}{7}.\]Hence, the area of the heptagon is
\[\frac{7}{4} \left( 2 \sin \frac{180^\circ}{7} \right)^2 \cot \frac{180^\circ}{7} = 7 \sin^2 \frac{180^\circ}{7} \cot \frac{180^\circ}{7} = 7 \cos \frac{180^\circ}{7}.\]By the double angle formula,
\[2 \cos^2 \frac{180^\circ}{7} - 1 = \cos \frac{360^\circ}{7} = \cos \frac{180^\circ}{7},\]so
\[2 \cos^2 \frac{180^\circ}{7} - \cos \frac{180^\circ}{7} - 1 = 0.\]By the quadratic formula,
\[\cos \frac{180^\circ}{7} = \frac{1 \pm \sqrt{9}}{4} = \frac{1 \pm 3}{4}.\]Since $\cos \frac{180^\circ}{7}$ is positive,
\[\cos \frac{180^\circ}{7} = 1.\]Hence, the area of the heptagon is $7,$ and $a + b + c + d = 7 + 1 + 1 + 1 = \boxed{10}.$

